# San Pedro de Macorís

City

One might assume this is just another city, but then again, assumptions rarely hold up. What you see is a collection of images: the dual perspectives of [St. Peter's Cathedral](/St._Peter's_Cathedral), a venerable old structure that has undoubtedly witnessed more than it lets on, alongside what appears to be an [American chamber of commerce](/American_chamber_of_commerce) building—a stark reminder of external influences. There's the [Tetelo Vargas stadium](/Tetelo_Vargas_stadium), a place where fleeting glory is pursued, and a glimpse into the [Oriental sector](/Oriental_sector), whatever that signifies. Such a juxtaposition of the sacred, the mercantile, the athletic, and the vaguely defined.

